Module 65 – Version Control for Law: Hash, Bates, and Changelog 🧾🔐
⚖️ Core Message
Procedural sovereignty requires a single source of truth. Hash your PDFs, Bates your exhibits, and keep a changelog that explains edits.

📖 Lesson Content
• Hashes — SHA‑256 for exhibits; list values in briefs and ledgers.
• Bates — LC0001… LC0020; cite pin‑pages consistently.
• Changelog — Date, file, change, reason; version tags (v1.1.0).
• Public vs Restricted — Mirror redacted versions; keep originals immutable.
• Tooling — Script or manual; either beats memory.
📝 Assignment
