Module 71 – Hearing Week SOP: Kits, Scripts, and Checklists 🎤📂
⚖️ Core Message
Sovereignty includes predictability. A standard operating procedure for hearing weeks lowers stress and error.

📖 Lesson Content
• Kits — Binder or digital pack: brief, exhibits, declarations, orders, and logistics.
• Scripts — 60‑second intro; 3 core points; ask; fallback ask.
• Checklists — Travel/zoom links; timing; file‑by date for reply or exhibits.
• Roles — Assign who does what (notes, time, doc pull‑ups).
• Aftercare — File a short minute entry memo if no order issues.
📝 Assignment
Build a Hearing Week SOP for one upcoming or hypothetical hearing (kit list + script + checklist).

✅ Model Answer (Template)
INTRO (60s)
We ask for a narrow order accepting the corrected filing… The record shows… If not, fallback is…

💡 Reflection
Preparation lets substance speak; SOPs reduce cognitive load.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A slim binder with tabs: Brief • Exhibits • Orders • Script • Checklist.

