Module 72 – Evidence Stacks: Declarations that Travel Across Motions 📚🧵
⚖️ Core Message
Avoid re‑inventing the wheel. Build modular declarations and exhibits that you can cite across multiple motions without conflict.

📖 Lesson Content
• Master Decl — Core timeline; references to exhibits; neutral tone.
• Motion Adds — Short add‑on declarations focused on the new relief.
• Exhibit Stacks — Reuse A–D; add E/F as needed; keep Bates consistent.
• Conflicts — Avoid changing facts; clarify with addenda rather than edits.
• Index — Declaration/exhibit map to avoid duplication.
📝 Assignment
