Module 87
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 7 — Procedural Memory & Public Archive
Module 87 – Archival Citation Standards: Make Memory Portable 🔗📑
⚖️ Core Message
Public memory breaks if citations do. Use portable citations: exhibit letters, Bates, hashes, and stable URLs (mirrors), in that order.

📖 Lesson Content
• Order — Ex./Bates first; docket second; mirrors last.
• Format — 'Ex. D at LC0012 (SHA‑256 3f2c…)'; link mirrors as convenience.
• Stability — Avoid transient URLs; archive snapshots; note access date.
• Readers — Put a 'How to Verify' box near the first citations.
• Consistency — Enforce one house style across all files.
📝 Assignment
Write a one‑page 'Citation Style' for your archive and apply it to five references in a brief.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
CITATION EXAMPLE
Ex. A at LC0003 (SHA‑256 9ab1…), Dkt. 25‑1 at 3.

💡 Reflection
Portable citations survive platform changes and legal copy/paste.

🎨 Visual Pairing
