Module 88 – Audio & Transcript Protocol: Capture What Was Said 🎙️🧾
⚖️ Core Message
If there’s no court transcript, create one. Use phone logs, public audio (if permitted), detailed notes, and declarations to memorialize key statements.

📖 Lesson Content
• Sources — Court audio (if allowed), personal notes, call logs, email confirmations.
• Format — Timestamped notes with speaker labels; declaration authenticating method.
• Request — Ask court for official transcript or permission to submit a statement under FRAP 10(c).
• Exhibit — Attach the notes/audio metadata with a custodian declaration.
• Privacy — Follow rules; never record unlawfully.
📝 Assignment
