Module 110 – Strategic Silence: When Not to Publish (Yet) 🤫⏳
⚖️ Core Message
Sometimes waiting preserves leverage: hold back until facts are verified, risks are mitigated, or filings are ready.

📖 Lesson Content
• Criteria — Unverified facts; unclear risk; pending negotiations; sensitive third‑party interests.
• Timers — Set review dates; don’t let silence become neglect.
• Interim — Share process (we’re verifying X) without details.
• Escrow — Prepare the pack; release when criteria met.
• Record — Log reasons for delay in a private note.
📝 Assignment
